{"questionListItems":[{"id":"clte0q0xu006j10z3sgwat9r2","title":"How do I pay my tax?","body":null,"createdAt":"2024-03-05T06:57:54.496Z","published":true,"publishedAt":"2024-03-05T06:57:54.450Z","priority":0,"answer":{"id":"clte0q0xu006k10z39fxqopvp","body":"<p>Income tax is payable within 1 month from the date of your tax bill. You may pay your tax via GIRO, AXS station or Internet Banking. Majority of our taxpayers pay their taxes by <a href=\"https://www.iras.gov.sg/quick-links/payments/giro-individual-income-tax\" title=\"GIRO\">GIRO</a>. Find out more about the different <a href=\"https://www.iras.gov.sg/quick-links/payments\" title=\"payment modes\">payment modes</a>.</p><p>If you are facing <a href=\"https://www.iras.gov.sg/taxes/individual-income-tax/basics-of-individual-income-tax/receive-tax-bill-pay-tax-check-refunds/experiencing-difficulties-in-paying-your-tax\" title=\"financial difficulties\">financial difficulties</a>, you may request for a longer payment plan via the ‘<a class=\"eyd-external-link\" href=\"https://mytax.iras.gov.sg/ESVWeb/default.aspx?target=MPYMApplyGIROBankDetails&amp;toLoginSelection=true\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Apply for Payment Plan\">Apply for Payment Plan</a>’ digital service at <a class=\"eyd-external-link\" href=\"https://mytax.iras.gov.sg/ESVWeb/default.aspx\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"myTax Portal\">myTax Portal</a> using your Singpass, upon receiving your tax bill, if you are paying by GIRO.</p>","updatedAt":"2024-03-05T06:57:54.496Z","numPositiveFeedback":0},"topics":[{"id":781,"title":"Individual Income Tax","priority":0,"agencyId":"cln4erax3001e5j0x1hjah8bj","parentTopicId":null,"parentTopic":null},{"id":1090,"title":"Tax Season 2024 - All you need to know","priority":0,"agencyId":"cln4erax3001e5j0x1hjah8bj","parentTopicId":781,"parentTopic":{"title":"Individual Income Tax"}}],"agency":{"code":"iras","logoUrl":"https://logos.ask.gov.sg/IRAS.png"}},{"id":"clte0q0xu006l10z3o18bfpf8","title":"When will I receive my tax bill?","body":null,"createdAt":"2024-03-05T06:57:54.496Z","published":true,"publishedAt":"2024-03-05T06:57:54.450Z","priority":0,"answer":{"id":"clte0q0xu006m10z3rpztnutw","body":"<p>Generally, most taxpayers should receive their <a href=\"https://www.iras.gov.sg/taxes/individual-income-tax/basics-of-individual-income-tax/receive-tax-bill-pay-tax-check-refunds/getting-my-tax-assessment\" title=\"Getting my tax assessment\">tax bills</a>, also known as Notice of Assessment (NOA), from end Apr 2024 to end Sep 2024. As IRAS sends out tax bills in batches, some taxpayers may receive them earlier than others. </p><p>If you have updated your Singapore mobile number with IRAS, you will receive an SMS alert when your tax bill is finalised. To update your mobile number, log in to <a class=\"eyd-external-link\" data-sf-ec-immutable=\"\" data-sf-marked=\"\" href=\"https://mytax.iras.gov.sg/ESVWeb/default.aspx\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"myTax Portal\">myTax Portal</a> using your <a class=\"eyd-external-link\" data-sf-ec-immutable=\"\" data-sf-marked=\"\" href=\"https://www.singpass.gov.sg/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Singpass\">Singpass</a> or <a href=\"https://www.iras.gov.sg/digital-services/others/singpass-foreign-user-account-(sfa)-for-foreign-individuals\" title=\"Singpass Foreign user Account (SFA)\">Singpass Foreign user Account (SFA)</a>, and click on 'Update Contact Details'. </p>","updatedAt":"2024-03-05T06:57:54.496Z","numPositiveFeedback":0},"topics":[{"id":781,"title":"Individual Income Tax","priority":0,"agencyId":"cln4erax3001e5j0x1hjah8bj","parentTopicId":null,"parentTopic":null},{"id":1088,"title":"Tax Season 2024 - About your tax bill","priority":0,"agencyId":"cln4erax3001e5j0x1hjah8bj","parentTopicId":781,"parentTopic":{"title":"Individual Income Tax"}}],"agency":{"code":"iras","logoUrl":"https://logos.ask.gov.sg/IRAS.png"}},{"id":"clte0q0xu006p10z37adip1vj","title":"What should I do when I receive my tax bill?","body":null,"createdAt":"2024-03-05T06:57:54.496Z","published":true,"publishedAt":"2024-03-05T06:57:54.450Z","priority":0,"answer":{"id":"clte0q0xu006q10z37tcb1xt1","body":"<p>You need to check and ensure that your <a href=\"https://www.iras.gov.sg/taxes/individual-income-tax/basics-of-individual-income-tax/what-is-taxable-what-is-not\" title=\"What is taxable, what is not\"></a><a href=\"https://www.iras.gov.sg/taxes/individual-income-tax/basics-of-individual-income-tax/what-is-taxable-what-is-not\" title=\"income details\">income details</a> and <a href=\"https://www.iras.gov.sg/taxes/individual-income-tax/basics-of-individual-income-tax/tax-reliefs-rebates-and-deductions\" title=\"relief claims\">relief claims</a> are accurate in your tax bill. If you have any other income that is not shown in your tax bill or if your relief claims (including those that are prefilled) are incorrect, please inform IRAS of any discrepancy through the “<a class=\"eyd-external-link\" data-sf-ec-immutable=\"\" href=\"https://mytax.iras.gov.sg/ESVWeb/default.aspx?target=MEObjHome&amp;toLoginSelection=true\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Object to Assessment\">Object to Assessment</a>” digital service in <a class=\"eyd-external-link\" data-sf-ec-immutable=\"\" href=\"https://mytax.iras.gov.sg/ESVWeb/default.aspx\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"myTax Portal\">myTax Portal</a> within 30 days from the date of your tax bill.</p>","updatedAt":"2024-03-05T06:57:54.496Z","numPositiveFeedback":0},"topics":[{"id":781,"title":"Individual Income Tax","priority":0,"agencyId":"cln4erax3001e5j0x1hjah8bj","parentTopicId":null,"parentTopic":null},{"id":1088,"title":"Tax Season 2024 - About your tax bill","priority":0,"agencyId":"cln4erax3001e5j0x1hjah8bj","parentTopicId":781,"parentTopic":{"title":"Individual Income Tax"}}],"agency":{"code":"iras","logoUrl":"https://logos.ask.gov.sg/IRAS.png"}},{"id":"clte0q0xu006r10z3xua6qeu0","title":"How do I submit an amendment to my tax bill online?","body":null,"createdAt":"2024-03-05T06:57:54.496Z","published":true,"publishedAt":"2024-03-05T06:57:54.450Z","priority":0,"answer":{"id":"clte0q0xv006s10z3p7np0mxm","body":"<p>You may use the “<a class=\"eyd-external-link\" data-sf-ec-immutable=\"\" data-sf-marked=\"\" href=\"https://mytax.iras.gov.sg/ESVWeb/default.aspx?target=MEObjHome&amp;toLoginSelection=true\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Object to Assessment\">Object to Assessment</a>” digital service at <a class=\"eyd-external-link\" data-sf-ec-immutable=\"\" data-sf-marked=\"\" href=\"https://mytax.iras.gov.sg/ESVWeb/default.aspx\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"myTax Portal\">myTax Portal</a> to file an objection for any of the following purposes:</p><ol><li>Revise income declaration;</li><li>Add or amend claims for deductions and reliefs;</li><li>Claim Parenthood Tax Rebate; or</li><li>Change in tax residency status (non-resident to resident, if applicable).</li></ol><p>This digital service allows you to easily view the pre-filled values in the original tax assessment and make amendments. Thereafter, you will be able to see a consolidated view of the revised income, deductions and reliefs and receive an instant acknowledgement upon submitting the objection. We will issue the revised tax bill (digital/paper) or provide an update on the status of your objection within 10 working days.</p>","updatedAt":"2024-03-05T06:57:54.496Z","numPositiveFeedback":0},"topics":[{"id":781,"title":"Individual Income Tax","priority":0,"agencyId":"cln4erax3001e5j0x1hjah8bj","parentTopicId":null,"parentTopic":null},{"id":1088,"title":"Tax Season 2024 - About your tax bill","priority":0,"agencyId":"cln4erax3001e5j0x1hjah8bj","parentTopicId":781,"parentTopic":{"title":"Individual Income Tax"}}],"agency":{"code":"iras","logoUrl":"https://logos.ask.gov.sg/IRAS.png"}},{"id":"clte0q0xv006t10z3ljld12ll","title":"What should I do if there is a discrepancy in my pre-filled employment income?","body":null,"createdAt":"2024-03-05T06:57:54.496Z","published":true,"publishedAt":"2024-03-05T06:57:54.450Z","priority":0,"answer":{"id":"clte0q0xv006u10z3fef3f90z","body":"<p><strong></strong>Please contact your employer directly to seek clarification. If there are subsequent amendments, your employer will transmit details of the amendments to IRAS. IRAS will send you the revised tax bill accordingly.</p>","updatedAt":"2024-03-05T06:57:54.496Z","numPositiveFeedback":0},"topics":[{"id":781,"title":"Individual Income Tax","priority":0,"agencyId":"cln4erax3001e5j0x1hjah8bj","parentTopicId":null,"parentTopic":null},{"id":1088,"title":"Tax Season 2024 - About your tax bill","priority":0,"agencyId":"cln4erax3001e5j0x1hjah8bj","parentTopicId":781,"parentTopic":{"title":"Individual Income Tax"}}],"agency":{"code":"iras","logoUrl":"https://logos.ask.gov.sg/IRAS.png"}},{"id":"clte0q0xv006v10z34pxms3k5","title":"How do I pay my tax?","body":null,"createdAt":"2024-03-05T06:57:54.496Z","published":true,"publishedAt":"2024-03-05T06:57:54.450Z","priority":0,"answer":{"id":"clte0q0xv006w10z349yjumxm","body":"<p>Income tax is payable within 1 month from the date of your tax bill. You may pay your tax via GIRO, AXS station or Internet Banking. Majority of our taxpayers pay their taxes by GIRO. Find out more about the different <a href=\"https://www.iras.gov.sg/quick-links/payments\" title=\"payment modes\">payment modes</a>.</p><p>If you are facing <a href=\"https://www.iras.gov.sg/taxes/individual-income-tax/basics-of-individual-income-tax/receive-tax-bill-pay-tax-check-refunds/experiencing-difficulties-in-paying-your-tax\" title=\"Experiencing difficulties in paying your tax?\">financial difficulties</a>, you may request for a longer payment plan via the ‘<a class=\"eyd-external-link\" data-sf-ec-immutable=\"\" data-sf-marked=\"\" href=\"https://mytax.iras.gov.sg/ESVWeb/default.aspx?target=MPYMApplyGIROBankDetails&amp;toLoginSelection=true\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Apply for Payment Plan\">Apply for Payment Plan</a>’ digital service at <a class=\"eyd-external-link\" data-sf-ec-immutable=\"\" data-sf-marked=\"\" href=\"https://mytax.iras.gov.sg/ESVWeb/default.aspx\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"myTax Portal\">myTax Portal</a> using your <a class=\"eyd-external-link\" data-sf-ec-immutable=\"\" data-sf-marked=\"\" href=\"https://www.singpass.gov.sg/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Singpass\">Singpass</a> upon receiving your tax bill, if you are under GIRO.</p>","updatedAt":"2024-03-05T06:57:54.496Z","numPositiveFeedback":0},"topics":[{"id":781,"title":"Individual Income Tax","priority":0,"agencyId":"cln4erax3001e5j0x1hjah8bj","parentTopicId":null,"parentTopic":null},{"id":1088,"title":"Tax Season 2024 - About your tax bill","priority":0,"agencyId":"cln4erax3001e5j0x1hjah8bj","parentTopicId":781,"parentTopic":{"title":"Individual Income Tax"}}],"agency":{"code":"iras","logoUrl":"https://logos.ask.gov.sg/IRAS.png"}},{"id":"clte0q0xv006x10z3h9ku8ivz","title":"What are the benefits of joining GIRO? How do I sign up?","body":null,"createdAt":"2024-03-05T06:57:54.496Z","published":true,"publishedAt":"2024-03-05T06:57:54.450Z","priority":0,"answer":{"id":"clte0q0xv006y10z3lh9t511c","body":"<p>GIRO is a fuss-free mode of paying your tax. You may choose to pay by monthly interest-free GIRO deductions (up to 12 months) or one (yearly) GIRO deduction. Find out more about <a href=\"https://www.iras.gov.sg/quick-links/payments\" title=\"GIRO\">GIRO</a>. </p>","updatedAt":"2024-03-05T06:57:54.496Z","numPositiveFeedback":0},"topics":[{"id":781,"title":"Individual Income Tax","priority":0,"agencyId":"cln4erax3001e5j0x1hjah8bj","parentTopicId":null,"parentTopic":null},{"id":1088,"title":"Tax Season 2024 - About your tax bill","priority":0,"agencyId":"cln4erax3001e5j0x1hjah8bj","parentTopicId":781,"parentTopic":{"title":"Individual Income Tax"}}],"agency":{"code":"iras","logoUrl":"https://logos.ask.gov.sg/IRAS.png"}},{"id":"clte0q0xv006z10z3xrhco1v3","title":"How do I get a refund for my tax credit?","body":null,"createdAt":"2024-03-05T06:57:54.496Z","published":true,"publishedAt":"2024-03-05T06:57:54.450Z","priority":0,"answer":{"id":"clte0q0xv007010z32kzloivr","body":"<p><strong></strong><span style=\"background-color: initial; font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; text-transform: inherit; white-space: inherit; word-spacing: normal; caret-color: auto\">You do not need to submit a claim for refund. More than 90% of the tax credits were refunded within 7 days from the date the credit arose.</span></p><p><span style=\"background-color: initial; font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; text-transform: inherit; white-space: inherit; word-spacing: normal; caret-color: auto\"></span><span style=\"background-color: initial; font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; text-transform: inherit; white-space: inherit; word-spacing: normal; caret-color: auto\">Taxpayers who pay taxes through GIRO will receive refunds in the form of tax credits through the same GIRO account. If you are using another person's bank account for GIRO payments, refunds will be made to you through cheques. Please deposit the cheque into your bank account within the 3 months’ validity period.</span></p>","updatedAt":"2024-03-05T06:57:54.496Z","numPositiveFeedback":0},"topics":[{"id":781,"title":"Individual Income Tax","priority":0,"agencyId":"cln4erax3001e5j0x1hjah8bj","parentTopicId":null,"parentTopic":null},{"id":1088,"title":"Tax Season 2024 - About your tax bill","priority":0,"agencyId":"cln4erax3001e5j0x1hjah8bj","parentTopicId":781,"parentTopic":{"title":"Individual Income Tax"}}],"agency":{"code":"iras","logoUrl":"https://logos.ask.gov.sg/IRAS.png"}},{"id":"clte0q0xv007310z331bgfic9","title":"I lost my tax bill. How can I get a copy of my tax bill?","body":null,"createdAt":"2024-03-05T06:57:54.496Z","published":true,"publishedAt":"2024-03-05T06:57:54.450Z","priority":0,"answer":{"id":"clte0q0xv007410z3cs4ujsw5","body":"<p>Visit <a class=\"eyd-external-link\" data-sf-ec-immutable=\"\" href=\"https://mytax.iras.gov.sg/ESVWeb/default.aspx\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"myTax Portal\">myTax Portal</a> to view or save a copy of your tax bill to your smartphone/ other devices, or print a copy of your tax bill. Find out more on <a href=\"https://www.iras.gov.sg/taxes/individual-income-tax/basics-of-individual-income-tax/receive-tax-bill-pay-tax-check-refunds/getting-my-tax-assessment\" title=\"Getting my tax assessment\">getting a copy of your tax bill and other documents</a>.</p>","updatedAt":"2024-03-05T06:57:54.496Z","numPositiveFeedback":0},"topics":[{"id":781,"title":"Individual Income Tax","priority":0,"agencyId":"cln4erax3001e5j0x1hjah8bj","parentTopicId":null,"parentTopic":null},{"id":1088,"title":"Tax Season 2024 - About your tax bill","priority":0,"agencyId":"cln4erax3001e5j0x1hjah8bj","parentTopicId":781,"parentTopic":{"title":"Individual Income Tax"}}],"agency":{"code":"iras","logoUrl":"https://logos.ask.gov.sg/IRAS.png"}},{"id":"cltc4dyth004xrb8nybzyr7tn","title":"I have received my tax bill for Year of Assessment 2024 and my bill is incorrect (e.g. overlooked to claim a tax relief or my income amount is lower). What should I do?","body":null,"createdAt":"2024-03-03T23:04:57.988Z","published":true,"publishedAt":"2024-03-03T23:04:57.951Z","priority":0,"answer":{"id":"cltc4dyth004yrb8n6gf8ny0v","body":"<p>Please make amendments to your income information and/or tax relief claims through the “Object to Assessment” digital service at <a class=\"eyd-external-link\" data-sf-ec-immutable=\"\" href=\"https://mytax.iras.gov.sg/ESVWeb/default.aspx\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"myTax Portal\">myTax Portal</a>. See details in Q4 of <a href=\"https://www.iras.gov.sg/taxes/individual-income-tax/basics-of-individual-income-tax/understanding-my-income-tax-filing/tax-season-2024---about-your-tax-bill\" title=\"Tax Season 2023 - About your tax bill\"></a><a href=\"https://www.iras.gov.sg/taxes/individual-income-tax/basics-of-individual-income-tax/understanding-my-income-tax-filing/tax-season-2024---about-your-tax-bill\">Tax Season 2024 – About your tax bill</a>\n</p>","updatedAt":"2024-03-03T23:04:57.988Z","numPositiveFeedback":0},"topics":[{"id":781,"title":"Individual Income Tax","priority":0,"agencyId":"cln4erax3001e5j0x1hjah8bj","parentTopicId":null,"parentTopic":null},{"id":794,"title":"General tax matters (for Singapore Citizens or PRs)","priority":0,"agencyId":"cln4erax3001e5j0x1hjah8bj","parentTopicId":781,"parentTopic":{"title":"Individual Income Tax"}}],"agency":{"code":"iras","logoUrl":"https://logos.ask.gov.sg/IRAS.png"}},{"id":"cltc4dyti0051rb8n1kv2b4g0","title":"How do I check if I need to file a tax return for the Year of Assessment 2024?","body":null,"createdAt":"2024-03-03T23:04:57.988Z","published":true,"publishedAt":"2024-03-03T23:04:57.951Z","priority":0,"answer":{"id":"cltc4dyti0052rb8nbxwlnrr8","body":"<p>Log in to <a class=\"eyd-external-link\" data-sf-ec-immutable=\"\" href=\"https://mytax.iras.gov.sg/ESVWeb/default.aspx\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"myTax Portal\">myTax Portal</a> with your Singpass/Singpass Foreign user Account (SFA) to check if IRAS has sent you a filing notification. At the Menu, select Individuals &gt; Filing Matters &gt; View Filing Status. Alternatively, you may use the <a href=\"https://www.iras.gov.sg/taxes/individual-income-tax/basics-of-individual-income-tax/understanding-my-income-tax-filing/filing-checker\" title=\"Filing Checker\">Filing Checker</a> to check if you need to file a tax return.</p><p>IRAS has introduced a Direct Notice of Assessment (D-NOA) initiative where taxpayers on the No-Filing Service scheme will get their tax bills directly. You may be selected for the D-NOA initiative if you only had auto-included income in the previous year. You do not need to file an Income Tax Return. Your tax bill will be computed based on your income provided by your employer and previous year’s relief claims.</p>","updatedAt":"2024-03-03T23:04:57.988Z","numPositiveFeedback":0},"topics":[{"id":781,"title":"Individual Income Tax","priority":0,"agencyId":"cln4erax3001e5j0x1hjah8bj","parentTopicId":null,"parentTopic":null},{"id":793,"title":"General tax matters (for Foreigner)","priority":0,"agencyId":"cln4erax3001e5j0x1hjah8bj","parentTopicId":781,"parentTopic":{"title":"Individual Income Tax"}}],"agency":{"code":"iras","logoUrl":"https://logos.ask.gov.sg/IRAS.png"}},{"id":"cltc4dyti0053rb8n7d06ku6j","title":"I changed job in 2023. Must I key in my employment income from the first employer?","body":null,"createdAt":"2024-03-03T23:04:57.988Z","published":true,"publishedAt":"2024-03-03T23:04:57.951Z","priority":0,"answer":{"id":"cltc4dyti0054rb8n8jxofhuq","body":"<p>You do not have to report employment income from the first employer if clearance has been sought on the said income. Refer to <a href=\"https://www.iras.gov.sg/taxes/individual-income-tax/employees/scenario-based-faqs-for-working-in-singapore-and-abroad/i-am-re-employed-in-singapore\" title=\"Re-employment in Singapore\">Re-employment in Singapore</a> for more details.</p>","updatedAt":"2024-03-03T23:04:57.988Z","numPositiveFeedback":0},"topics":[{"id":781,"title":"Individual Income Tax","priority":0,"agencyId":"cln4erax3001e5j0x1hjah8bj","parentTopicId":null,"parentTopic":null},{"id":793,"title":"General tax matters (for Foreigner)","priority":0,"agencyId":"cln4erax3001e5j0x1hjah8bj","parentTopicId":781,"parentTopic":{"title":"Individual Income Tax"}}],"agency":{"code":"iras","logoUrl":"https://logos.ask.gov.sg/IRAS.png"}},{"id":"cltc4dyti0055rb8n2fxu79wp","title":"I retired in March 2024 this year and have no income since then. However, I received a notification to file for the Year of Assessment 2024. What should I do?","body":null,"createdAt":"2024-03-03T23:04:57.988Z","published":true,"publishedAt":"2024-03-03T23:04:57.951Z","priority":0,"answer":{"id":"cltc4dyti0056rb8nvq6fs0ge","body":"Income tax is assessed on a preceding calendar year basis. The notification to file for the Year of Assessment (YA) 2024 is for you to file for the income earned by you in 2023. You will be required to file an income tax return for YA 2024 if you have received a letter, form or SMS from IRAS informing you to do so.","updatedAt":"2024-03-03T23:04:57.988Z","numPositiveFeedback":0},"topics":[{"id":781,"title":"Individual Income Tax","priority":0,"agencyId":"cln4erax3001e5j0x1hjah8bj","parentTopicId":null,"parentTopic":null},{"id":1101,"title":"Individuals required to file tax","priority":0,"agencyId":"cln4erax3001e5j0x1hjah8bj","parentTopicId":781,"parentTopic":{"title":"Individual Income Tax"}}],"agency":{"code":"iras","logoUrl":"https://logos.ask.gov.sg/IRAS.png"}},{"id":"clsi45mjq008dksb6ngkk8jda","title":"Do I submit the income information of taxable employees only?","body":null,"createdAt":"2024-02-11T23:05:23.558Z","published":true,"publishedAt":"2024-02-11T23:05:23.533Z","priority":0,"answer":{"id":"clsi45mjq008eksb6ljzf3ycd","body":"<p>You are required to prepare and submit the employment income information for <strong>all</strong> employees regardless of the income amount.</p>","updatedAt":"2024-02-11T23:05:23.558Z","numPositiveFeedback":0},"topics":[{"id":781,"title":"Individual Income Tax","priority":0,"agencyId":"cln4erax3001e5j0x1hjah8bj","parentTopicId":null,"parentTopic":null},{"id":1096,"title":"AIS - Employees to be Included in AIS Submission","priority":0,"agencyId":"cln4erax3001e5j0x1hjah8bj","parentTopicId":781,"parentTopic":{"title":"Individual Income Tax"}}],"agency":{"code":"iras","logoUrl":"https://logos.ask.gov.sg/IRAS.png"}},{"id":"clsi45mjq008fksb6aa28vzjv","title":"As a new AIS employer who joined AIS in YA 2024, can I electronically submit amendment to back year’s employment income information (i.e. YA 2023) if I have previously overstated the employees’ income in their Form IR8As?","body":null,"createdAt":"2024-02-11T23:05:23.558Z","published":true,"publishedAt":"2024-02-11T23:05:23.533Z","priority":0,"answer":{"id":"clsi45mjq008gksb6m8qfh8ds","body":"You should prepare and provide the hardcopy revised Form IR8A to your employees for back year’s adjustments made to employment income information. You should also <a href=\"https://www.iras.gov.sg/contact-us/individual-income-tax#title4\">email IRAS</a> with the relevant information of the affected employee(s) by using the <a href=\"https://www.iras.gov.sg/media/docs/default-source/uploadedfiles/xlsx/ir8a-template-for-omission-of-income-for-ais.xlsx\">Excel Template</a>.<br/>","updatedAt":"2024-02-11T23:05:23.558Z","numPositiveFeedback":0},"topics":[{"id":781,"title":"Individual Income Tax","priority":0,"agencyId":"cln4erax3001e5j0x1hjah8bj","parentTopicId":null,"parentTopic":null},{"id":1096,"title":"AIS - Employees to be Included in AIS Submission","priority":0,"agencyId":"cln4erax3001e5j0x1hjah8bj","parentTopicId":781,"parentTopic":{"title":"Individual Income Tax"}}],"agency":{"code":"iras","logoUrl":"https://logos.ask.gov.sg/IRAS.png"}}],"webResult":null,"count":214,"agency":{"id":"cln4erax3001e5j0x1hjah8bj","name":"Inland Revenue Authority of Singapore","code":"iras","homepageUrl":"https://www.iras.gov.sg","enquiryPageUrl":null,"scope":"GLOBAL","emailDomainWhitelist":[],"type":"OFFICIAL","minimumDayResponseTime":5,"responseTimeRange":2,"logoUrl":"https://logos.ask.gov.sg/IRAS.png","searchHint":"what is Stamp Duty for?","description":null,"trendingTerms":[],"hasSubjectTriaging":true,"subjects":[{"id":"clq62uyga0004k4brxfll23bq","title":"Individual Income Tax"},{"id":"clq62uyga0006k4brebl42gk5","title":"Property Tax"},{"id":"clq62uyga0005k4bro7tr2cfa","title":"Stamp Duty"}]},"currentPage":4,"matchedTokens":null,"agencyTopics":[{"id":781,"qcount":144,"title":"Individual Income Tax","agencyId":